<p><a href="https://www.gchq.gov.uk/files/gchq%20christmas%20challenge%202025.pdf">This year&#8217;s GCHQ Christmas Challenge is now live.</a> Devised by Government Communications Headquarters, the British intelligence agency, this year&#8217;s quiz presents seven puzzles for children aged 11-18. They&#8217;re designed to test a range of problem-solving skills, including creativity and intuitive reasoning. </p>
<p>Agency director Anne Keast-Butler said: &#8220;Puzzles are at the heart of GCHQ&#8217;s work to keep the country safe from hostile states, terrorists and criminals; challenging our teams to think creatively and analytically every day.&#8221;</p>
